5751 /******************************************************************************/
5752 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
5753 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
5754 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
5755 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
5756 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
5757 /******************************************************************************/
5758 
5759 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
5760 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
5761 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQn DMA1_Channel1_IRQn
5762 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQn DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQn
5763 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
5764 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
5765 #define RCC_CRS_IRQn RCC_IRQn
5766 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQn TIM6_IRQn
5767 #define USART3_8_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
5768 #define USART3_6_IRQn USART3_4_IRQn
5769 
5770 
5771 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
5772 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
5773 #define DMA1_Ch1_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel1_IRQHandler
5774 #define DMA1_Ch2_3_DMA2_Ch1_2_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel2_3_IRQHandler
5775 #define DMA1_Ch4_7_DMA2_Ch3_5_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
5776 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
5777 #define RCC_CRS_IRQHandler RCC_IRQHandler
5778 #define TIM6_DAC_IRQHandler TIM6_IRQHandler
5779 #define USART3_8_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
5780 #define USART3_6_IRQHandler USART3_4_IRQHandler
5781 
5782 
5783 #ifdef __cplusplus
5784 }
5785 #endif /* __cplusplus */
5786
